WEBVTT

1
00:02:35.948 --> 00:02:37.115
<font color="#fecb00">For you. Doctor.</font>

2
00:02:38.116 --> 00:02:39.867
<font color="#fecb00">I'm supposed to wear this?</font>

3
00:02:39.868 --> 00:02:41.786
<font color="#fecb00">No. You're supposed to eat it.</font>

4
00:02:41.787 --> 00:02:44.790
<font color="#fecb00">I thought you might be hungry.
so I picked you up some along the way.</font>

5
00:02:45.332 --> 00:02:47.584
<font color="#fecb00">Yeah. you're supposed to wear it. Kei.</font>

6
00:02:48.669 --> 00:02:50.336
<font color="#fecb00">A little torqued up. Doc. huh?</font>

7
00:02:50.337 --> 00:02:52.547
<font color="#fecb00">Well. this dress prevents breathing.</font>

8
00:02:52.548 --> 00:02:54.090
<font color="#fecb00">and these shoes prevent walking.</font>

9
00:02:54.091 --> 00:02:57.718
<font color="#fecb00">and I'm expected to impress men
who can't remember my name</font>

10
00:02:57.719 --> 00:02:59.470
<font color="#fecb00">and would just as soon shut us down</font>

11
00:02:59.471 --> 00:03:01.223
<font color="#fecb00">as turn our work into weaponry.</font>

12
00:03:02.057 --> 00:03:03.183
<font color="#fecb00">Why isn't Billy here?</font>

13
00:03:04.268 --> 00:03:06.812
<font color="#fecb00">Are you kidding me?
He'd look terrible in that dress.</font>

14
00:03:08.856 --> 00:03:10.815
<font color="#fecb00">Look. this is only one night a year...</font>

15
00:03:10.816 --> 00:03:13.317
<font color="#fecb00">- All right.
- ...okay? So. we say hello.</font>

16
00:03:13.318 --> 00:03:15.403
<font color="#fecb00">say thank you
to the people who are footing the bill.</font>

17
00:03:15.404 --> 00:03:17.947
<font color="#fecb00">- and then we can go on our merry way.
- Right. Okay.</font>

18
00:03:17.948 --> 00:03:19.116
<font color="#fecb00">Exhale.</font>

19
00:03:19.741 --> 00:03:20.742
<font color="#fecb00">Smile.</font>

20
00:03:22.536 --> 00:03:25.330
<font color="#fecb00">- And-- Thank you.
- Yeah.</font>

21
00:03:26.707 --> 00:03:28.000
<font color="#fecb00">- Have a drink.
- Yes.</font>

22
00:03:35.799 --> 00:03:36.800
<font color="#fecb00">Or three.</font>

23
00:03:42.181 --> 00:03:45.224
<font color="#fecb00">Captain Lee Shaw.</font>

24
00:03:45.225 --> 00:03:47.143
<font color="#fecb00">I ever tell you
about this son of a bitch?</font>

25
00:03:47.144 --> 00:03:49.520
<font color="#fecb00">Unguided missile. this kid.</font>

26
00:03:49.521 --> 00:03:52.899
<font color="#fecb00">I pulled him out of a bar brawl.</font>

27
00:03:52.900 --> 00:03:56.611
<font color="#fecb00">He was all busted up. bloody knuckles.</font>

28
00:03:56.612 --> 00:03:58.155
<font color="#fecb00">But potential.</font>

29
00:03:59.489 --> 00:04:00.615
<font color="#fecb00">Real potential.</font>

30
00:04:00.616 --> 00:04:02.742
<font color="#fecb00">I saw great things for you. didn't I?</font>

31
00:04:02.743 --> 00:04:03.868
<font color="#fecb00">Yes. sir.</font>

32
00:04:03.869 --> 00:04:08.665
<font color="#fecb00">Do you remember what I told you
to do to succeed in this man's army?</font>

33
00:04:09.249 --> 00:04:11.501
<font color="#fecb00">- You remember. Leland?
- Definitely. sir.</font>

34
00:04:11.502 --> 00:04:15.380
<font color="#fecb00">You said to only punch
sailors and marines from now on.</font>

35
00:04:19.134 --> 00:04:20.177
<font color="#fecb00">That's what you said.</font>

36
00:04:25.307 --> 00:04:26.641
<font color="#fecb00">Now look at you.</font>

37
00:04:26.642 --> 00:04:30.646
<font color="#fecb00">A captain with the future
of Project Monarch in your hands.</font>

38
00:04:31.146 --> 00:04:33.773
<font color="#fecb00">We're excited to hear more about
this mysterious Project Monarch.</font>

39
00:04:33.774 --> 00:04:34.899
<font color="#fecb00">Outstanding.</font>

40
00:04:34.900 --> 00:04:38.402
<font color="#fecb00">I think that you'll find our work
vital to not only American security</font>

41
00:04:38.403 --> 00:04:41.323
<font color="#fecb00">but global scientific superiority.</font>

42
00:04:41.907 --> 00:04:44.408
<font color="#fecb00">And I'd like to introduce you
to the brains of our outfit.</font>

43
00:04:44.409 --> 00:04:45.702
<font color="#fecb00">Dr. Keiko Miura.</font>

44
00:04:46.620 --> 00:04:48.539
<font color="#fecb00">- Pleasure to see you again. Doctor.
- General.</font>

45
00:04:49.039 --> 00:04:50.498
<font color="#fecb00">Thank you. Captain.</font>

46
00:04:50.499 --> 00:04:53.084
<font color="#fecb00">Miura? Japanese name. yeah?</font>

47
00:04:53.085 --> 00:04:55.546
<font color="#fecb00">Hey. Now. she's one of the good ones.</font>

48
00:05:11.436 --> 00:05:12.688
<font color="#fecb00">"One of the good ones."</font>

49
00:05:14.064 --> 00:05:15.731
<font color="#fecb00">- Puckett...
- General Puckett.</font>

50
00:05:15.732 --> 00:05:18.318
<font color="#fecb00">- ...is a major asshole.
- Hey. you gotta keep your voice down.</font>

51
00:05:19.695 --> 00:05:20.696
<font color="#fecb00">Okay?</font>

52
00:05:21.405 --> 00:05:26.326
<font color="#fecb00">Hey. guys like them.
they are old-fashioned.</font>

53
00:05:27.744 --> 00:05:30.204
<font color="#fecb00">If we ever find another Titan.</font>

54
00:05:30.205 --> 00:05:32.456
<font color="#fecb00">those old-fashioned men will blow it up</font>

55
00:05:32.457 --> 00:05:34.334
<font color="#fecb00">- or march it into Red Square.
- Kei.</font>

56
00:05:39.506 --> 00:05:40.507
<font color="#fecb00">Yeah.</font>

57
00:05:41.633 --> 00:05:45.761
<font color="#fecb00">Have you ever heard the expression
"To a hammer. the whole world is a nail"?</font>

58
00:05:45.762 --> 00:05:46.847
<font color="#fecb00">Yeah.</font>

59
00:05:47.931 --> 00:05:49.892
<font color="#fecb00">Well. this is a hardware store.</font>

60
00:05:53.103 --> 00:05:55.730
<font color="#fecb00">Yeah. Well. in my country.
we have a saying.</font>

61
00:05:55.731 --> 00:05:58.317
<font color="#fecb00">"The nail that sticks up
gets hammered down."</font>

62
00:06:02.446 --> 00:06:03.447
<font color="#fecb00">Not you.</font>

63
00:06:05.199 --> 00:06:06.658
<font color="#fecb00">No. you're gonna change their minds.</font>

64
00:06:08.285 --> 00:06:10.245
<font color="#fecb00">as old-fashioned as they may be.</font>

65
00:06:11.872 --> 00:06:13.040
<font color="#fecb00">How?</font>

66
00:06:14.124 --> 00:06:15.417
<font color="#fecb00">'Cause it's what you do.</font>

67
00:06:17.461 --> 00:06:18.670
<font color="#fecb00">It's who you are. Kei.</font>

68
00:06:20.964 --> 00:06:22.174
<font color="#fecb00">You are a...</font>

69
00:06:23.967 --> 00:06:25.135
<font color="#fecb00">force of nature.</font>

70
00:06:46.573 --> 00:06:47.574
<font color="#fecb00">Come on.</font>

71
00:06:49.117 --> 00:06:51.036
<font color="#fecb00">The things I do for Monarch.</font>

72
00:07:35.956 --> 00:07:36.957
<font color="#fecb00">What?</font>

73
00:08:01.190 --> 00:08:03.233
<font color="#fecb00">- What are you doing?
- Dipping you.</font>

74
00:08:07.821 --> 00:08:08.906
<font color="#fecb00">They're watching.</font>

75
00:09:26.275 --> 00:09:28.317
{\an8}<font color="#fecb00">You could be one of them. you know.</font>

76
00:09:28.318 --> 00:09:30.696
{\an8}<font color="#fecb00">Maybe General Puckett's right.</font>

77
00:09:31.655 --> 00:09:34.408
<font color="#fecb00">Being career military might not be so bad.</font>

78
00:09:35.993 --> 00:09:37.160
<font color="#fecb00">More nights like this.</font>

79
00:09:38.787 --> 00:09:39.830
<font color="#fecb00">A life like this.</font>

80
00:09:42.499 --> 00:09:43.624
<font color="#fecb00">A house.</font>

81
00:09:43.625 --> 00:09:44.710
<font color="#fecb00">Neighbors.</font>

82
00:09:46.461 --> 00:09:48.922
<font color="#fecb00">Barbecues in the backyard
with the neighbors.</font>

83
00:09:49.548 --> 00:09:51.717
<font color="#fecb00">- Sunday luncheons with the girls.
- Yeah.</font>

84
00:09:53.218 --> 00:09:54.261
<font color="#fecb00">- Kids.
- Kids.</font>

85
00:10:08.150 --> 00:10:10.277
<font color="#fecb00">Do you know what my favorite thing
about children is?</font>

86
00:10:12.321 --> 00:10:13.989
<font color="#fecb00">Never afraid to say "I don't know."</font>

87
00:10:15.240 --> 00:10:19.703
<font color="#fecb00">Everything. every day.
is an adventure and a mystery.</font>

88
00:10:21.538 --> 00:10:22.956
<font color="#fecb00">They devour the world.</font>

89
00:10:25.250 --> 00:10:27.290
<font color="#fecb00">Wanna know what my favorite thing
about children is?</font>

90
00:10:29.087 --> 00:10:30.547
<font color="#fecb00">Making 'em.</font>

91
00:10:43.018 --> 00:10:44.561
<font color="#fecb00">Captain Shaw?</font>

92
00:10:45.687 --> 00:10:47.689
<font color="#fecb00">It's a slow elevator.</font>

93
00:10:49.775 --> 00:10:51.318
<font color="#fecb00">Captain Shaw?</font>

94
00:10:52.653 --> 00:10:55.238
<font color="#fecb00">Urgent message for Captain Lee Shaw...</font>

95
00:10:55.239 --> 00:10:57.449
<font color="#fecb00">- No.
- ...from Bill Randa.</font>

96
00:10:58.325 --> 00:10:59.535
<font color="#fecb00">No. Don't do this to me.</font>

97
00:11:04.706 --> 00:11:06.333
<font color="#fecb00">Maybe next luau. soldier.</font>

98
00:11:13.924 --> 00:11:14.925
<font color="#fecb00">I'm Shaw.</font>

99
00:11:18.929 --> 00:11:20.764
<font color="#fecb00">The things I do for Monarch.</font>

100
00:11:58.302 --> 00:11:59.344
<font color="#fecb00">Duvall?</font>

101
00:12:02.556 --> 00:12:03.557
<font color="#fecb00">Help me up?</font>

102
00:12:04.099 --> 00:12:05.975
<font color="#fecb00">- What's--
- This is the old man. yes?</font>

103
00:12:05.976 --> 00:12:07.269
<font color="#fecb00">Change of plan.</font>

104
00:12:08.312 --> 00:12:10.479
<font color="#fecb00">Colonel. your dossier
says you speak French.</font>

105
00:12:10.480 --> 00:12:12.482
<font color="#fecb00">If this is true. clear your throat.</font>

106
00:12:14.735 --> 00:12:18.197
<font color="#fecb00">Excellent. Count to six. then drop.</font>

107
00:12:43.388 --> 00:12:44.681
<font color="#fecb00">Clean.</font>

108
00:12:54.608 --> 00:12:56.817
<font color="#fecb00">Another Titan emergence is coming.</font>

109
00:12:56.818 --> 00:12:59.446
<font color="#fecb00">You think you know how to stop it.
but Monarch disagrees.</font>

110
00:13:01.198 --> 00:13:04.116
<font color="#fecb00">Why do you know more
than the finest physicists.</font>

111
00:13:04.117 --> 00:13:07.287
<font color="#fecb00">geologists. and zoologists on Earth?</font>

112
00:13:08.247 --> 00:13:09.706
<font color="#fecb00">Don't know more...</font>

113
00:13:10.791 --> 00:13:13.043
<font color="#fecb00">but I got a good idea
about what's going on.</font>

114
00:13:16.463 --> 00:13:18.882
<font color="#fecb00">Didn't do enough about that
when I had the chance.</font>

115
00:13:19.842 --> 00:13:21.552
<font color="#fecb00">Figuring I was making up for that now</font>

116
00:13:22.970 --> 00:13:24.303
<font color="#fecb00">or die in the trying.</font>

117
00:13:24.304 --> 00:13:26.806
<font color="#fecb00">Why not share what you know with Monarch?
Surely they could help.</font>

118
00:13:26.807 --> 00:13:29.141
<font color="#fecb00">They've known everything for years.</font>

119
00:13:29.142 --> 00:13:32.396
<font color="#fecb00">I've been telling them for years.</font>

120
00:13:33.230 --> 00:13:35.607
<font color="#fecb00">They just don't believe it.</font>

121
00:13:36.275 --> 00:13:38.861
<font color="#fecb00">- Why not?
- Because I'm crazy.</font>

122
00:13:39.736 --> 00:13:42.864
<font color="#fecb00">Just like wild Bill Randa
and his crazy kid Hiro.</font>

123
00:13:42.865 --> 00:13:44.616
<font color="#fecb00">I mean. it's amazing. isn't it?</font>

124
00:13:45.117 --> 00:13:50.163
<font color="#fecb00">How anyone who disagrees with them
has gotta be just crazy.</font>

125
00:13:57.421 --> 00:13:59.089
<font color="#fecb00">What about you. mademoiselle?</font>

126
00:14:02.259 --> 00:14:03.302
<font color="#fecb00">My sister. Sandra.</font>

127
00:14:04.178 --> 00:14:05.429
<font color="#fecb00">She worked in Japan.</font>

128
00:14:07.139 --> 00:14:08.140
<font color="#fecb00">Janjira.</font>

129
00:14:12.603 --> 00:14:16.315
<font color="#fecb00">Some of us came to Monarch
saying "Never again."</font>

130
00:14:17.816 --> 00:14:18.817
<font color="#fecb00">I meant it.</font>

131
00:14:20.444 --> 00:14:25.407
<font color="#fecb00">And there are more who feel like me.
waiting for someone to show us how.</font>

132
00:14:28.619 --> 00:14:29.995
<font color="#fecb00">I think it's you.</font>

133
00:14:33.790 --> 00:14:35.000
<font color="#fecb00">Does that make me crazy?</font>

134
00:14:38.795 --> 00:14:41.673
<font color="#fecb00">I think you and I
have a lot to talk about.</font>

135
00:15:03.737 --> 00:15:05.071
<font color="#fecb00">Hey. Sorry for interrupting</font>

136
00:15:05.072 --> 00:15:07.824
<font color="#fecb00">your big whatever-the-hell-it-was
I-don't-give-a-shit.</font>

137
00:15:09.284 --> 00:15:11.954
<font color="#fecb00">- but I think we got a live one.
- Visual confirmation?</font>

138
00:15:12.496 --> 00:15:14.872
<font color="#fecb00">A guy thinks he saw it but isn't sure.</font>

139
00:15:14.873 --> 00:15:16.913
<font color="#fecb00">- Sounds squirrelly--
- What kind of a data are we--</font>

140
00:15:17.209 --> 00:15:19.127
<font color="#fecb00">- Sorry. Doctor.
- Beg your pardon. Captain.</font>

141
00:15:21.797 --> 00:15:22.798
<font color="#fecb00">Okay.</font>

142
00:15:23.423 --> 00:15:25.842
<font color="#fecb00">Hey. I don't know how you do
what you do. Kei.</font>

143
00:15:25.843 --> 00:15:27.844
<font color="#fecb00">but I know
that when the little squiggly line</font>

144
00:15:27.845 --> 00:15:30.972
<font color="#fecb00">shoots off the top of the page like that.
it means something.</font>

145
00:15:30.973 --> 00:15:34.768
<font color="#fecb00">The only other time I've seen
isotopic signatures like this</font>

146
00:15:35.894 --> 00:15:36.895
<font color="#fecb00">was in the Philippines.</font>

147
00:15:38.397 --> 00:15:39.939
<font color="#fecb00">It's what led us
to the wreck of the Lawton.</font>

148
00:15:39.940 --> 00:15:41.482
<font color="#fecb00">So. this is a Titan?</font>

149
00:15:41.483 --> 00:15:43.109
<font color="#fecb00">It's not definitively not a Titan.</font>

150
00:15:43.110 --> 00:15:45.487
<font color="#fecb00">Okay. that's definitively not an answer.</font>

151
00:15:46.071 --> 00:15:47.822
<font color="#fecb00">If it's not one of our bogies.
then what is it?</font>

152
00:15:47.823 --> 00:15:50.158
<font color="#fecb00">The three most beautiful words
