153
00:15:51.952 --> 00:15:53.619
<font color="#fecb00">I don't know.</font>

154
00:15:53.620 --> 00:15:55.497
<font color="#fecb00">- We need to get to Japan.
- Yes.</font>

155
00:15:59.209 --> 00:16:00.376
<font color="#fecb00">Now?</font>

156
00:16:00.377 --> 00:16:03.588
<font color="#fecb00">We're presenting our budget proposal
to the committee on Friday.</font>

157
00:16:03.589 --> 00:16:05.548
<font color="#fecb00">- You heard General Puckett.
- Puckett?</font>

158
00:16:05.549 --> 00:16:07.341
<font color="#fecb00">Titans don't care about
budget meetings. Lee.</font>

159
00:16:07.342 --> 00:16:10.386
<font color="#fecb00">That's because Titans
don't have to sing for their supper. Kei.</font>

160
00:16:10.387 --> 00:16:12.347
<font color="#fecb00">But you know who's got
a beautiful singing voice?</font>

161
00:16:13.682 --> 00:16:15.725
<font color="#fecb00">Perfect. We'll divide and conquer.</font>

162
00:16:15.726 --> 00:16:17.602
<font color="#fecb00">You stay and deal with the hardware store.</font>

163
00:16:17.603 --> 00:16:19.395
<font color="#fecb00">- and--
- No.</font>

164
00:16:19.396 --> 00:16:22.191
<font color="#fecb00">I'm not letting you
go on a Titan hunt alone.</font>

165
00:16:24.276 --> 00:16:26.819
<font color="#fecb00">- Or you. Both of you.
